WEBVTT

00:00.752 --> 00:02.459
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:02.521 --> 00:06.435
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:06.491 --> 00:08.300
the police
who investigate crime

00:08.360 --> 00:11.136
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:11.196 --> 00:12.675
These are their stories.

00:14.399 --> 00:15.707
(LAUGHING)

00:16.335 --> 00:18.212
I've been lied to by experts.

00:18.270 --> 00:23.083
Like I said, no wife, no
roommates, no live-ins.

00:23.975 --> 00:25.113
No problems, baby.

00:25.177 --> 00:26.178
(LAUGHING)

00:26.244 --> 00:27.314
(MOANING)

00:28.547 --> 00:29.548
Oh.

00:30.048 --> 00:31.152
Red lipstick?

00:31.216 --> 00:32.217
(SIGHING)

00:32.951 --> 00:34.055
My mother's.

00:34.119 --> 00:35.257
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

00:40.292 --> 00:43.364
You want a drink,
baby? Wine?

00:43.495 --> 00:46.066
Uh-huh. A glass of red
wine would be nice.

00:46.131 --> 00:47.166
All right.

00:50.602 --> 00:52.548
Are you sure
you're not married?

00:52.604 --> 00:54.481
Last time I checked.

00:54.673 --> 00:55.981
(FRIDGE DOOR OPENING)

00:56.808 --> 00:57.980
(FRIDGE DOOR CLOSING)

00:58.043 --> 00:59.249
(BOTTLES CLINKING)

01:01.046 --> 01:02.150
(BEEPING)

01:02.214 --> 01:05.058
WOMAN OVER SPEAKER: I did it. You
don't have to worry anymore.

01:05.784 --> 01:06.854
I killed Dee-Dee.

01:06.918 --> 01:08.022
(BEEPS)

01:09.554 --> 01:10.760
Here we go.

01:10.822 --> 01:12.859
I just remembered, there's
someplace I gotta be.

01:12.924 --> 01:14.460
Oh, Come on, baby.
What's the matter?

01:14.526 --> 01:15.596
RATTINGER: No.

01:15.660 --> 01:17.230
Stop it! Stop it!
Come on.

01:17.295 --> 01:18.569
What?
(GASPS)

01:19.865 --> 01:21.003
Come on.

01:21.500 --> 01:24.947
Hey, what did I do?
Come on, now!

01:25.003 --> 01:26.038
(SIGHS)

01:26.938 --> 01:29.077
The message said,
"I killed her."

01:29.141 --> 01:30.779
Are you sure you heard right?

01:30.876 --> 01:33.880
(CLEARING THROAT) I mean, you said
yourself, you'd had a few drinks.

01:34.079 --> 01:37.185
This guy had someone killed.
It said so on the machine.

01:37.649 --> 01:38.889
And where can we find him?

01:38.950 --> 01:42.022
You know that big building on the
corner of Riverside and 114th?

01:42.087 --> 01:43.794
Well, that's where he lives.

01:43.855 --> 01:45.198
Okay.

01:45.557 --> 01:46.627
What's his name?

01:47.292 --> 01:48.532
Stanley.

01:48.927 --> 01:52.170
He said he was a fashion photographer,
but I don't know where.

01:52.230 --> 01:54.369
Okay, let me see
if I got this straight.

01:54.433 --> 01:58.506
Stanley somebody, who's a
fashion photographer someplace,

01:58.570 --> 02:03.280
lives in some apartment, probably in
a building at 114th and Riverside

02:03.341 --> 02:06.288
and has a message about
the murder of somebody

02:06.344 --> 02:07.755
who might be
named Dee-Dee.

02:07.913 --> 02:08.983
That's right.

02:09.548 --> 02:11.323
Yeah, thanks for coming in.

02:11.383 --> 02:13.420
You think you could describe
him to our sketch artist?

02:13.819 --> 02:14.889
Yes.
Good.

02:14.953 --> 02:17.160
You wait here.
We'll bring someone.

02:17.389 --> 02:19.027
Oh, this is gonna be
a slam dunk, Rey.

